{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"weedy-lath-abbey","description":"# WS7 ŌĆö Make Gerrit the only path into GitHub `main` (cutover) + contributor guide\n\n## Why\nComplete the dogfood: GitHub `main` must only advance via Gerrit's replication identity, so every\nchange is gated by the `LLM-Review` review-bot (WS6) before it can land. Today the repo still\ncarries its legacy branch protection and devs still open GitHub PRs; there is also **no dev-facing\nguide** for the Gerrit contribution flow (only setup/ops docs). WS7 flips the switch and documents\nthe new flow.\n\n## Context ŌĆö CONSUMES d251/S6 (do not rebuild)\n`d251`'s S6 (`075f`, closed) already built the mechanism:\n- `infra/terraform-github/` ŌĆö the repo-level ruleset with a **DeployKey-only bypass** (the\n  `rebar-gerrit-replication` key from S5) on `main` (+ tags): `update` (which rejects BOTH direct\n  pushes AND PR merges by non-bypass actors) + `deletion` + `non_fast_forward`.\n- `infra/runbooks/github-mirror-lock.md` ŌĆö the cutover & rollback runbook.\n- `infra/github/main-protection.snapshot.json` ŌĆö a snapshot of the **pre-existing `main-protection`\n  ruleset (id 18048287)** for rollback.\n\nWS7 EXECUTES/finalizes that cutover on `navapbc/rebar` and reconciles any legacy protection ŌĆö it\ndoes not re-author the ruleset or Terraform.\n\n## What\n1. **Remove the legacy protection + activate the Gerrit-only ruleset.** Ensure the pre-existing\n   `main-protection` ruleset (18048287) and any other human/PR-merge path is removed/superseded so\n   the SOLE ruleset governing `main` is the S6 DeployKey-only lock. Reconcile with the S6 Terraform\n   so state matches (no drift, no second competing ruleset).\n2. **Contributor guide** ŌĆö a repo-root `CONTRIBUTING.md` (the doc gap): the Gerrit remote setup, the\n   `Change-Id` commit-msg hook, `git push origin HEAD:refs/for/main`, how the single `LLM-Review`\n   vote gates submit, how to read a `-1` (a real finding vs a `coverage-gap` infra veto ŌĆö the WS6\n   message tags), how to amend + re-push a patchset, submit, and that **GitHub is a read-only\n   mirror** (direct pushes / PR merges are rejected). Linked from `README`.\n3. **Live cutover apply + proof** (gated on GitHub admin access): apply the ruleset change and\n   verify a direct push / PR-merge to `main` is rejected AND a Gerrit-submitted change replicates\n   to GitHub `main`.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: reconciling/removing the legacy `main` protection to the single Gerrit-only ruleset; the\n  `CONTRIBUTING.md` contributor guide; the live apply + verification.\n- OUT: re-authoring S6's ruleset/Terraform/runbook (done); the review-bot decision wiring (WS6);\n  provisioning Gerrit/replication (d251).\n\n## Boundary (honest)\nThe **live apply** needs a token with `Administration:write` on `navapbc/rebar` and is a\nhigh-impact, mirror-locking change. If that access is not available in this session, the config\nreconcile plan + the `CONTRIBUTING.md` are still deliverable; the live apply + proof are surfaced\nas blocked (do NOT fake the cutover) ŌĆö analogous to WS6-b's live-env boundary.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n### Doable now (no live GitHub admin)\n- [ ] A repo-root `CONTRIBUTING.md` documents the full Gerrit contribution flow (remote + Change-Id hook + `push ŌĆ”:refs/for/main` + the `LLM-Review` vote semantics incl. finding-vs-coverage-gap `-1` + amend/re-push + submit + GitHub-is-a-mirror); linked from `README`.\n- [ ] The cutover plan names the exact legacy ruleset(s) to remove (incl. `main-protection` id 18048287) and confirms the S6 DeployKey-only ruleset is the sole remaining `main` protection; reconciled against the S6 Terraform (no drift / no competing ruleset).\n### Live-gated (needs `Administration:write` on `navapbc/rebar`)\n- [ ] The legacy protection is removed and the Gerrit-only ruleset is active on `navapbc/rebar` `main` (+ tags).\n- [ ] Proof recorded on this ticket: a direct GitHub push / PR-merge to `main` is REJECTED, and a change submitted in Gerrit replicates to GitHub `main`.\n\n## Dependencies\n- CONSUMES d251/S6 (`075f`, closed) tooling + the S5 replication deploy key.\n- relates_to WS6 (the review-bot must be voting before Gerrit-only enforcement is meaningful).","id":"1bd2-1401-3a18-4031","parent_id":"b744-4fb9-2d05-4b49","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"WS7: Make Gerrit the only path into GitHub main (cutover) + contributor guide"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782868153840791001,"uuid":"e42e8e00-7697-4a2d-bcab-3cae34ee7cc5"}